<subSubSection id="C32D6512C042ED4EBA8EFEC09D1A2363" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B883699C042ED4EBA8EFEC09C7C274D" blockId="9.[226,1362,259,364]" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">
Description: Body length 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC042ED4EB8CFFEC09D5A273E" box="[675,826,259,287]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.65" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="7.65" valueMax="7.8" valueMin="7.5">7.5-7.8 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC042ED4EBE57FEC09AC0273E" box="[1083,1184,259,287]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC042ED4EBA8EFEEA9F242764" box="[226,324,297,325]" captionStart="Figs 14-20" captionStartId="10.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[231,1351,249,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-51@10.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 14-20: Lathrobium hartmanni nov.sp.: (14) habitus; (15) forebody; (16) male sternite VII; (17) male sternite VIII; (18-19) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (20) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 14-15: 1.0 mm; 16-20: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518399/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
. Coloration: body blackish-brown; legs, except for the paler tarsi, dark-brown; antennae reddish-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C042ED4EBA8EFE439D582417" blockId="9.[226,1362,384,566]" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">
Head (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC042ED4EBB57FE439FFB27BD" box="[315,411,384,412]" captionStart="Figs 14-20" captionStartId="10.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[231,1351,249,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-51@10.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 14-20: Lathrobium hartmanni nov.sp.: (14) habitus; (15) forebody; (16) male sternite VII; (17) male sternite VIII; (18-19) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (20) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 14-15: 1.0 mm; 16-20: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518399/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) as long as broad; punctation moderately coarse and moderately dense, slightly sparser in median dorsal portion; interstices with distinct microreticulation, on average somewhat broader than diameter of punctures. Eyes weakly projecting from lateral contours of head, approximately 1/3 the length of postocular region in dorsal view and composed of approximately 30 ommatidia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C042ED4EBA8EFD899B3024AC" blockId="9.[226,1361,586,653]" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC042ED4EBB19FD899FB52447" box="[373,469,586,614]" captionStart="Figs 14-20" captionStartId="10.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[231,1351,249,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-51@10.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 14-20: Lathrobium hartmanni nov.sp.: (14) habitus; (15) forebody; (16) male sternite VII; (17) male sternite VIII; (18-19) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (20) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 14-15: 1.0 mm; 16-20: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518399/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.18 times as long as broad and as broad as head; punctation similar to that of head, but slightly coarser; interstices without microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C042ED4EBA8EFD629DA4252B" blockId="9.[226,1362,673,778]" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">
Elytra short, approximately 0.55 times as long as pronotum (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC042ED4EBE61FD629A10249C" box="[1037,1136,673,701]" captionStart="Figs 14-20" captionStartId="10.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[231,1351,249,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-51@10.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 14-20: Lathrobium hartmanni nov.sp.: (14) habitus; (15) forebody; (16) male sternite VII; (17) male sternite VIII; (18-19) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (20) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 14-15: 1.0 mm; 16-20: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518399/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); humeral angles weakly marked; punctation shallow; interstices without distinct microsculpture. Hind wings completely reduced. Metatibia slightly compressed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C042ED4EBA8EFCDC9F22258F" blockId="9.[226,1362,799,942]" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Abdomen broader than elytra; punctation moderately fine and dense, somewhat sparser on posterior than on anterior tergites; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe; posterior margin of tergite VIII weakly convex to indistinctly pointed in the middle.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C042ED4EBA8EFC019B7F22E4" blockId="9.[226,1361,962,1221]" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">
♂: protarsomeres I-IV strongly dilated; sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC042ED4EB9EBFC019D8325FF" box="[903,995,962,990]" captionStart="Figs 14-20" captionStartId="10.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[231,1351,249,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-51@10.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 14-20: Lathrobium hartmanni nov.sp.: (14) habitus; (15) forebody; (16) male sternite VII; (17) male sternite VIII; (18-19) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (20) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 14-15: 1.0 mm; 16-20: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518399/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) shallowly impressed posteriorly and with sparse long black setae in postero-median portion, posterior margin weakly concave; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC042ED4EB8E5FBCC9C8C220A" box="[649,748,1039,1067]" captionStart="Figs 14-20" captionStartId="10.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[231,1351,249,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-51@10.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 14-20: Lathrobium hartmanni nov.sp.: (14) habitus; (15) forebody; (16) male sternite VII; (17) male sternite VIII; (18-19) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (20) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 14-15: 1.0 mm; 16-20: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518399/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) moderately transverse, with shallow median impression, this impression with weakly modified black setae, posterior excision small, not very deep, and anteriorly concave; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC042ED4EB90FFB9F9D902259" box="[867,1008,1116,1144]" captionStart="Figs 14-20" captionStartId="10.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[231,1351,249,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-51@10.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 14-20: Lathrobium hartmanni nov.sp.: (14) habitus; (15) forebody; (16) male sternite VII; (17) male sternite VIII; (18-19) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (20) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 14-15: 1.0 mm; 16-20: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518399/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Figs 18-19</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC042ED4EBE68FB9F9A052259" box="[1028,1125,1116,1144]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long, ventral process weakly curved in lateral view and gradually narrowed apicad in ventral view, dorsal plate lamellate and moderately sclerotised, internal sac with a long membranous tube.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C042ED4EBA8EFB239D1A2363" blockId="9.[226,1361,1241,1346]" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">
<specimenCount id="9D31FD10C042ED4EBA8EFB239E9C22DD" box="[226,252,1248,1276]" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: protarsomeres I-IV strongly dilated; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC042ED4EB9FEFB1A9D8F22D4" box="[914,1007,1241,1269]" captionStart="Figs 14-20" captionStartId="10.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[231,1351,249,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-51@10.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 14-20: Lathrobium hartmanni nov.sp.: (14) habitus; (15) forebody; (16) male sternite VII; (17) male sternite VIII; (18-19) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (20) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 14-15: 1.0 mm; 16-20: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518399/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) oblong and with smoothly convex posterior margin; tergite IX undivided anteriorly; tergite X approximately as long as antero-median portion of tergite IX in the middle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32D6512C042ED4EBA8EFA949A2A2087" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B883699C042ED4EBA8EFA949A2A2087" blockId="9.[226,1362,1367,1702]" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">
Comparative notes: Based on the external and male sexual characters, 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC042ED4EBF5BFA949F0623B8" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hartmanni">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC042ED4EBF5BFA949F0623B8" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">L. hartmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC042ED4EB840FABE9CB223B8" box="[556,722,1405,1433]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">L. muguicum</emphasis>
species group, which previously included only 
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC042ED4EBF5BFABE9F0623E1" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">L. muguicum</emphasis>
, whose female sexual characters are unknown. Both species are externally extremely similar. The new species is distinguished from 
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC042ED4EB9ABFA099A0E23C7" box="[967,1134,1482,1510]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">L. muguicum</emphasis>
by the somewhat darker legs (
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC042ED4EBBE9FA339C4D202D" box="[389,557,1520,1548]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">L. muguicum</emphasis>
: legs and antennae reddish), the broader and not distinctly Vshaped posterior excision of the male sternite VIII, and particularly by the morphology of the aedeagus. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC042ED4EBBD0F9FE9C032078" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[444,611,1597,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hartmanni">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC042ED4EBBD0F9FE9C032078" box="[444,611,1597,1625]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">L. hartmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the aedeagus is smaller (
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC042ED4EB9DDF9FE9A382078" box="[945,1112,1597,1625]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">L. muguicum</emphasis>
: 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC042ED4EBE07F9FE9AB12078" box="[1131,1233,1597,1625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
), the ventral process is apically abruptly narrowed (ventral view), stouter (lateral view), apically curved, and somewhat truncate, and the internal tube is less massive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32D6512C042ED4EBA8EF9789A912105" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B883699C042ED4EBA8EF9789A912105" blockId="9.[226,1362,1723,1828]" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">
Distribution and natural history: The type locality is situated to the southeast of the Saipal peak in Bajhang district, 
<collectingRegion id="49F3F87BC042ED4EB9F9F9229A2420DC" box="[917,1092,1761,1789]" country="Nepal" name="Seti" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Seti province</collectingRegion>
, northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F3207609C042ED4EBF6AF9229B3220DC" box="[1286,1362,1761,1789]" name="Nepal" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Nepal</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC042ED4EBA87F8CB9F222105" box="[235,322,1800,1828]" captionStart="Map 2" captionStartId="6.[226,283,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[226,1340,1372,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-368@6.[226,1341,1400,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Map 2: Type localities of Lathrobium uttaricum nov.sp. (triangle), L. hartmanni nov.sp. (circle), and L. makaluicum nov.sp. (diamond)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518395/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="256">Map 2</figureCitation>
). The specimens were collected near a river bank at an altitude of 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC042ED4EBEE6F8CB9A8D2105" box="[1162,1261,1800,1828]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" pageId="9" pageNumber="256" unit="m" value="3750.0">3750 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
